Node.Notes: ""Sacrifices of strife" should be translated as something like "feasting with strife.""
Appears to describe reality of how a bribe works. Pr17:23 clearly condemns bribery.
"To meet" from first half is carried over.
(SYNTAX) A dislocated np, referred back to by "him." Could not promote to np and then cl again because ClCl directly gets priority in processing.
The overall meaning of this verse is something like "The start of a quarrel is like a water leak. So stop quarreling before it breaks out."
Uncertain what "making high his opening" means. Could be elaborate entrance/gate (that invites thieves and/or shows pride) or perhaps proud speech ("opening" extended metaphorically to "mouth").
